Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) national leaders are cross-crossing Mpumalanga’s Lowveld region ahead of the party’s sixth anniversary rally. It will be held at the 15 000 seating capacity KaNyamazane stadium on Saturday. The EFF’s National Communications Manager Sixo Gcilishe they are interacting with the community. “We understand locals need water and the road infrastructure needs attention as some can’t even get to hospitals on time because ambulances cannot get to where they are. We will make submissions in Parliament. The naysayers thought we wouldn’t make it past two years, today we are celebrating six years, and therefore tomorrow it’s a celebration of many things.” Party leader Julius Malema will deliver the keynote address. Watch related video: